      <p>These luminous nocturnal insects are prized by miners and adventurers. They have two glands, one above each eye, that produce a red glow. The glands' luminosity persists for 1d6 days after removal from the beetle, illuminating a roughly circular area with a 10-foot radius. <a href="ch74s04.html#MonstersVermin12">Giant fire beetles</a> are about 2 feet long.</p>
